description: This data on travel time and means of transportation for commuters traveling to work comes from the U.S. Census Bureau's American Community Survey (ACS) one-year estimates, which are published on an annual basis.  It includes data for the following cities: Tampa, Florida; Memphis, Tennessee; Louisville, Kentucky; Nashville, Tennessee; Raleigh, North Carolina; Atlanta, Georgia; Baton Rouge, Louisiana; New Orleans, Louisiana. This data covers the time period of 2005 to present.
